<subSubSection id="C32EC7FEBA6C9D06FD37FC26FF06FEDB" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B9475BA6C9D05FD37FC26FCD3FA2B" blockId="25.[699,1228,868,1741]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
COMMENTS: In the original description, Brehm said that 
<emphasis id="B9404867BA6C9D05FC6AFBC4FB9FFBE3" box="[901,1056,1044,1067]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
V. 
<taxonomicName id="4C34EFF6BA6C9D05FC46FBC4FB9FFBE3" box="[937,1056,1044,1067]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Oenanthe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leucopyga">leucopyga</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was from the same locality as 
<emphasis id="B9404867BA6C9D05FC65FBE1FBA5FB80" box="[906,1050,1073,1096]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">V. monacha</emphasis>
, which is that given above, and that the name was based on the manuscript name, 
<taxonomicName id="4C34EFF6BA6C9D05FC2DFBBCFB1DFB4B" box="[962,1186,1132,1155]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lucotoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucopyga">
<emphasis id="B9404867BA6C9D05FC2DFBBCFB1DFB4B" box="[962,1186,1132,1155]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lucotoa leucopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of Paul de Wrttbg (5 Württemberg). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA5E984BA6C9D05FB96FB59FCECFB75" author="Hartert, E." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="641 - 817" refId="ref96226" refString="Hartert, E. 1910 a. Die Vogel der Palaarktischen Fauna, Band 1, heft 6: 641 - 817, XIII - XLIX. Berlin: R. Friedlander." type="journal article" year="1910">Hartert (1910a: 699)</bibRefCitation>
noted that he was only able to be sure of this name by studying the type and referring to A.E. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA5E984BA6C9D05FC71FB31FB3CFB30" author="Brehm, A. E." box="[926,1155,1249,1272]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="46 - 69" refId="ref90772" refString="Brehm, A. E. 1858. Die Sanger Spaniens. Journal fur Ornithologie 6: 46 - 69." type="journal article" year="1858">Brehm (1858: 66)</bibRefCitation>
, who there gave the name as 
<taxonomicName id="4C34EFF6BA6C9D05FC3AFB2FFB74FADE" box="[981,1227,1279,1302]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lutucoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucopygaia">
<emphasis id="B9404867BA6C9D05FC3AFB2FFB74FADE" box="[981,1227,1279,1302]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lutucoa leucopygaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and credits Paul de Württemberg with the description. Three additional specimens labeled 
<taxonomicName id="4C34EFF6BA6C9D05FD54FA87FC84FAA6" box="[699,827,1367,1390]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Lucotoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucopyga">
<emphasis id="B9404867BA6C9D05FD54FA87FC84FAA6" box="[699,827,1367,1390]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">leucopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Brehm are 
<typeStatus id="548F2AD7BA6C9D05FBE2FA86FB77FAA5" box="[1037,1224,1366,1389]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
: AMNH 455144 and 455145, collected at Abu­Hammed in 
<collectingCountry id="F323D4E5BA6C9D05FC76FA41FBA8FA60" box="[921,1047,1425,1448]" name="Sudan" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">the Sudan</collectingCountry>
in 1849, and AMNH 455147, collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F323D4E5BA6C9D05FBF2FA7EFB28FA0D" box="[1053,1175,1454,1477]" name="Sudan" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">the Sudan</collectingCountry>
, but without a date.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B9475BA6C9D06FD37FA39FF06FEDB" blockId="25.[699,1228,868,1741]" lastBlockId="26.[124,653,193,275]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<materialsCitation id="3B5C9E28BA6C9D06FD37FA39FE62FF10" collectorName="von Korosko' &amp; A. E. Brehm's" country="Egypt" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" location="Egypt" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" specimenCount="2">
A pencilled note on the Rothschild label in hand unknown reads: ‘‘Erlegungsort nicht weit nordlich 
<collectorName id="26C1F1A3BA6C9D05FCB0F9F4FBB6F9F3" box="[863,1033,1572,1595]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">von Korosko’</collectorName>
’. This is perhaps the basis for 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA5E984BA6C9D05FCB4F991FBEEF990" author="Vaurie, C." box="[859,1105,1601,1624]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref106827" refString="Vaurie, C. 1959. The birds of the Palearctic fauna. Passeriformes. London: H. F. &amp; G. Witherby, 762 pp." type="book" year="1959">Vaurie’s (1959: 353)</bibRefCitation>
statement that the 
<typeStatus id="548F2AD7BA6C9D05FCF2F98EFCF0F9BD" box="[797,847,1630,1653]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
was collected near Kurusku (5 Korosko), 228359N, 328239E (Times Atlas), 
<collectingCountry id="F323D4E5BA6C9D05FD54F949FCBCF978" box="[699,771,1689,1712]" name="Egypt" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, thus restricting the 
<typeStatus id="548F2AD7BA6C9D05FBFDF949FBFBF978" box="[1042,1092,1689,1712]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
locality. I traced this to 
<collectorName id="26C1F1A3BA6C9D05FC84F966FBB0F905" box="[875,1039,1718,1741]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">A.E. Brehm’s</collectorName>
account of his travels in 
<collectingCountry id="F323D4E5BA6F9D06FF15FF11FEF9FF10" box="[250,326,193,216]" name="Sudan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Sudan</collectingCountry>
, 1847–1852
</materialsCitation>
; on 
<date id="FF8AB2B5BA6F9D06FDF8FF11FF09FF3D" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1850-03-31">31 March 1850</date>
he was in Korosko (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA5E984BA6F9D06FE1CFF0EFF13FEDB" author="Arndt" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref90202" refString="Arndt, H. (editor). 1975. Alfred Edmund Brehm Reisen im Sudan 1847 bis 1852. Tubingen: Horst Erdmann Verlag, 412 pp." type="book" year="1975">Arndt, 1975: 259</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
